# Memory system cleanup

Sequel to [Memory System Repair](../memory-system-repair/memory-system-repair-brief.svx):
the five judgment calls Joel resolved in the 2026-07-17 grilling become
execution, plus a full fleet skill/prompt update so no standing rule,
skill, or graft block references the retired machinery. Joel chartered
and authorized execution in one breath ("charter and execute cleanup and
full fleet skill/prompt update", 2026-07-17).

## Finish line

- The legacy memory stack is retired as ONE migration with receipts:
  `joelclaw recall` (and the voice recall tool) answer from the
  Brain/observation stores; `memory_observations` is snapshotted to NAS
  and dropped from live Typesense; the reflect/promote/proposal zombie
  functions are unregistered; the MEM/FRIC suites are deleted. The
  system log retires in the same migration: panda's JSONL snapshotted to
  NAS, the slog write path / system-logger / sync + backup + PDS-mirror
  hooks removed.
- Chorus is parked: no briefing injection at session start, the
  13-mutation outbox is preserved-then-discarded (file snapshot before
  discard), the service is stopped with a receipt.
- Claude auto-memory is a pointer index: non-duplicated facts from the
  18 topic pages live as Brain `.svx`; `MEMORY.md` is a binding rule +
  one-line pointers; topic pages deleted.
- The retro writer exists: claude/codex/pi hooks can send an Inngest
  event with pointers; a condenser function writes a retro `.svx` where
  the curator reads; the noise bar from the decision is enforced.
- The fleet is coherent: dark-wizard graft blocks, skills, TOOLS.md, and
  repo CLAUDE.md content mention none of the retired surfaces as live;
  changes are committed, pushed, and grafted (`fleet-graft.sh install`),
  so blaine/panda pick them up on next sync.
- The [memory system page](../../resources/memory-system.svx) is
  regenerated from post-cleanup reality (this also satisfies the repair
  brief's page-regeneration finish line), rebuilt on the wiki, 200-checked,
  and the link DM'd.

## Vocabulary

- **retired** — code paths removed or unregistered, data snapshotted to
  NAS before any deletion, receipts in the step file.
- **parked** — service stopped and disabled, nothing deleted, restart
  path documented.
- **pointer index** — `MEMORY.md` carries a binding rule plus one-line
  pointers to Brain pages; no content lives there.
- **fleet coherent** — a grep for the retired surface across dark-wizard
  fleet content and skills finds only historical/archival mentions.

## Notes

- Decisions of record (all closed 2026-07-17):
  [legacy retirement](../memory-system-repair/decide-legacy-memory-retirement.svx),
  [system log](../memory-system-repair/decide-system-log-home.svx),
  [Chorus](../memory-system-repair/decide-chorus-fate.svx),
  [auto-memory](../memory-system-repair/decide-claude-auto-memory.svx),
  [retro writer](../memory-system-repair/decide-retro-writer.svx).
  Workers cite these and the review's
  [periphery survey](../memory-system-review/periphery-survey.svx); no
  re-deciding.
- Execution authorization (Joel, 2026-07-17): build + deploy on flagg;
  steering reviews, commits, deploys with receipts. Raw-data deletion
  only after NAS snapshot receipts exist; no force-push; panda touched
  read-only except the snapshot copy.
- Concurrency: the repair effort's outbox drain continues in parallel;
  both efforts touch `packages/system-bus` — steering serializes commits.
  Workers edit only their own step file and named outputs.
- Skills: `herdr-orchestration` (fan-out), `flagg-workloads` (worker
  restart mechanics), wiki law `joelclaw-wiki/AGENTS.md` (page regen).

